p.span: Governor Polis has updated his executive order that schools will be closed until April 30th.

span.style: font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(28, 30, 33);

p.span:
We will continue educational material distribution through April 30th as you were previously notified in the letter sent out on March 23rd. Meals distribution will continue through April 30th as you were previously notified.
Click here for more on the update.

span.style: font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(28, 30, 33);

p.span: We are going to wear blue on Wednesdays to show support! If you would like to show off your support send in pictures to our face book page and we will post them on Wednesdays!

p.style: margin: 4.5pt 0in; background: white none repeat scroll 0% 50%; line-height: normal; -moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; -moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; -moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial;

span.style: font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(28, 30, 33);

p.span: Also here is a site if you would like to learn more about Autism:

span.style: font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);
font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;

p.span: CCSD RE-5 School District will still be distributing educational materials to parents and students on Monday April 13th. Below is a letter explaining how we will distribute due to inclement weather. Food distribution will also continue as scheduled. Please know we are exempt from the governor's executive order.

span.a: Letter for material distribution Monday April 13th.

span.style: font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);
font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;

p.span: Letter to the Certified Staff, Classified Staff, and Parents

span.style: font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);
font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;

p.span: Please click on this link to read the letter that explains how we are continuing education through the 30th of April and beyond if necessary.

span.style: font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);
font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;
font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);
font-size: 18pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;

p.span: The school will be providing breakfast/lunches on Mondays and Wednesdays for ages children ages 0 to 18. Please call and schedule your time. 767-5656 ext. 1045

span.style: font-size: 20pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: rgb(255, 102, 0);
font-size: 12pt; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;

p.span: Please call Gloria Donnelly by no later than Wednesday of each week to tell her if you are participating for the next week breakfast/lunch. We will continue as long as our staff is healthy, to April 30th, or beyond if needed.

span.style: font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;

p.span: Please pick up food between 11:30 - 12:00. Remember to display your number in the windshield and bring a box. Stay in your vehicle if someone is in front of you. Please allow time for the distribution table to be sanitized and food placed on the table before you get out of your car. Thank you for keeping yourself and our helpers healthy.
